    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-21T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="281"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.24/622: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-21T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 21, 1943—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 9:51 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>189. Department’s 150, July 20, 4 p.m. The Subsecretary of National Defense
                    states that an order for 1000 sub-machine guns has been placed with the
                    Harrington and Richardson Arms Company Worcester, Massachusetts, upon the
                    recommendation of the Salvadoran Military Attaché. He added that this equipment
                    is required by the national guard (about 800 men) and army officers, to replace
                    obsolescent guns. He made no mention of a request for such material addressed to
                    the Coast Guard.</p>
                <p>As the Department is aware from my reports, it appears to be the intention to
                    amend the Salvadoran Constitution to facilitate General Martínez continuation in
                    the Presidency for a fourth term. It is possible that opposition to this plan
                    may develop and that this particular type of weapon may be desired for the
                    repression of civil disorders.</p>
                <pb facs="0325" n="311" xml:id="pg_311"/>
                <p>I have requested the Military Attaché<note n="6" xml:id="d281fn6">Maj. Charles P.
                        Baldwin.</note> to investigate through different channels and I shall
                    forward his report by airgram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
